# Vercel Web Analytics Implementation

## Summary
Successfully implemented Vercel Web Analytics for the ResumeGen React + Vite application.

## Changes Made

### 1. Installed Dependencies
- Added `@vercel/analytics` package to the project
- Updated `package.json` with the new dependency
- Updated `package-lock.json` with dependency resolution

### 2. Modified Files
- **src/App.jsx**: Added Vercel Analytics integration
  - Imported `Analytics` component from `@vercel/analytics/react`
  - Placed `<Analytics />` component inside the `<BrowserRouter>` wrapper, after the `<Routes>` component
  - This placement ensures analytics tracking works properly with React Router for route detection

## Implementation Details

The Analytics component was added to the main App component following the Vercel Web Analytics documentation for React applications. The implementation:

1. **Import**: Added `import { Analytics } from "@vercel/analytics/react";` at the top of App.jsx
2. **Placement**: Added `<Analytics />` component inside the BrowserRouter, ensuring it has access to routing context
3. **Position**: Placed after the Routes component to ensure all routing is set up before analytics initialization

## Technical Decisions

- **Framework-specific package**: Used `@vercel/analytics/react` instead of the generic package for better React integration
- **Component placement**: Positioned inside BrowserRouter to enable automatic route tracking with React Router
- **No route tracking note**: The documentation mentions that plain React implementation doesn't have automatic route support, but with React Router integration, route changes will be tracked

## Build Verification

✅ Build completed successfully with `npm run build`
✅ All dependencies installed properly
✅ No new linting errors introduced (1 pre-existing error in AuthContext.jsx unrelated to this change)

## Next Steps for Users

After deploying to Vercel:
1. Enable Web Analytics in the Vercel dashboard (Project → Analytics tab → Enable)
2. Deploy the app using `vercel deploy` or via Git integration
3. Verify analytics by checking for `/_vercel/insights/view` requests in browser Network tab
4. View analytics data in the Vercel dashboard under the Analytics tab

## Notes

- The Analytics component will automatically track page views and visitor data
- Route changes will be tracked automatically due to React Router integration
- Analytics data will only be visible after deployment to Vercel
- The implementation follows Vercel's official documentation for React applications
